"Patch the Package:\n"
"------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:221
msgid ""
"After you unpack the tarball and change to the heimdal-0.6.2 directory, you "
"must make a change to a library header file, the configure script and "
"several documentation files so that the installation does not look for some "
"files in a /var/heimdal directory. To make the installation FHS compliant "
"and use /var/lib/heimdal instead, you can use a sed script or a patch. I've "
"provided both."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:223
msgid "To make the required changes using sed, here's the command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:227 origin/heimdal.txt:839
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"sed -i -e \"s@var/heimdal@var/lib/heimdal@g\" configure.in configure \\\n"
"    doc/setup.texi doc/heimdal.info-1 kadmin/kadmind.8 kdc/kdc.8 \\\n"
"    lib/hdb/hdb.h lib/krb5/krb5.conf.5 lib/krb5/krb5.conf.cat5\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:229
msgid "To make the required changes using a patch, here's the command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:231 origin/heimdal.txt:843
msgid "patch -Np1 -i ../heimdal-0.6.2-fhs-compliance-1.patch"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:234
msgid ""
"To have the Heimdal package link against the cracklib library, you must "
"apply a patch. Install the patch with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:236
msgid "patch -Np1 -i ../heimdal-0.6.2-cracklib-1.patch"
msgstr ""

