"You may try \"make -k check\" and see if it will run through. I did this and "
"it skipped the rest of the \"appl\" directory after the error on the "
"\"xnlock\" program. Be sure to log your output if you want to view the "
"results (unless you have an extraordinary amount of scroll buffer on your "
"terminal)."
msgstr ""

