#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1142
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Configuring PAM:\n"
"----------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1148
msgid ""
"There are many examples of PAM configuration files in the pam.d subdirectory "
"of the source tree. Additionally, the README file in the source tree is full "
"of good information. Please review this information for configuring your PAM "
"installation for use with Kerberos."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1151
msgid ""
"Correctly configured, the pam_krb5 module will almost eliminate the need to "
"manually acquire a TGT."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1154
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Configuring /etc/heimdal/krb5.conf\n"
"----------------------------------\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1158
msgid ""
"To fully utilize the pam_krb5 module you should add a section the Heimdal "
"configuration file, /etc/heimdal/krb5.conf. Insert the following lines:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1173
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[appdefaults]\n"
"    pam = {\n"
"        keytab = /etc/heimdal/krb5.keytab\n"
"        debug = true\n"
"        ticket_lifetime = 36000\n"
"        renew_lifetime = 36000\n"
"        forwardable = true\n"
"        krb4_convert = true\n"
"        afs_cells = FQDN_of_KDC_server\n"
"        hosts = FQDN_of_additional_hosts\n"
"        max_timeout = 30\n"
"        timeout_shift = 2\n"
"        initial_timeout = 1\n"
"    }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/heimdal.txt:1176
msgid ""
"You should modify or remove any lines appropriate to your installation.  "
"Insure you modify the lines containing FQDN."
